2x2 board can have a max of 1 queen because the queen invalidates the horizontal, vertical and diagonal spaces.\
\
3x3 board can have a max of 2 queens. Once you place the first queen on the board, there are only two remaining possible places for queens, but both spots are diagonals of each other. Once a diagonal is taken, it invalidates the other diagonal.\
\
4x4 board can have a max of 4 queens. I figured this out in class, it was relatively simple. I also noticed three things: the L shape of keeping the queens as close together as possible, the post symmetry, and you cannot have a queen in the corner spots.\
\
5x5 board is just an extension of the 4x4 board, with an additional queen in the top left corner or bottom right corner. It can have a max of 5 queens.\
\
